The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Day I Highlights
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Day I Highlights
                      
	 Mahendra Singh Dhoni became the 31st player to lead India in a Test         
	 He also became the first wicketkeeper to lead India in a Test and the 25th to lead a Test side in international cricket. Sri Lanka are the only country not to have a keeper captain ever in a Test         
	 Piyush Chawla last played a Test (his debut) versus England in Mohali (March 2006). At 17 years and 75 days, Chawla was the second youngest to play for India         
	 When they were 50 for no loss, South Africa brought up their sixth consecutive opening partnership of at least 50 runs. The details are:         
	 52  McKenzie/Smith vs Ban (Mirpur, 2007-08)         
	 415  McKenzie/Smith vs Ban (Chittagong, 2007-08)         
	 132  Smith/McKenzie vs Ind (Chepauk, 2007-08)         
	 53  McKenzie/Smith vs Ind (Chepauk, 2007-08)         
	 78  Smith/McKenzie vs Ind (Ahmedabad, 2007-08)         
	 61  McKenzie/Smith vs Ind (Kanpur, 2007-08)               
	 Smith scored his 22nd Test half-century and his sixth against India. He equalled Andrew Hudson as the South African with most fifties against India         
	 With Morne Morkels catch, Rahul Dravid equalled Stephen Fleming (171 catches) in the No.2 spot as the fielders with most catches. Mark Waugh (181) heads the list                                                                                                                          
